  "ai_profile": "**Down The Rabbit Hole 2026: A Wonderland of Sound and Culture**  \n\nTaking place from July 3–5, 2026, *Down The Rabbit Hole* returns with a boundary-pushing lineup of 194 artists, representing a kaleidoscope of genres and global sounds. With a strong emphasis on electronic music (29 artists) and experimental sounds (11 artists), the festival promises a sonic journey from pulsating techno beats to atmospheric ambient soundscapes. Fans of indie rock, disco, house, and hip-hop will also find plenty to love, with these genres each represented by a diverse group of performers. The lineup balances cutting-edge trends like hyperpop and experimental electronics with timeless styles such as folk, punk, soul, and world music.\n\nThis year’s edition celebrates its global outlook, featuring artists from 30 countries. A strong contingent of Dutch talent (71 acts) reflects the festival’s homegrown roots, while performers from the UK (24), the US (15), France (6), and Italy (6) add an international flair. The festival’s commitment to diversity shines through, with performers hailing from countries as far-flung as Nigeria, Jamaica, Thailand, and DR Congo, showcasing an exciting blend of cultural influences.  \n\nChampioning inclusivity, *Down The Rabbit Hole 2026* highlights a wide range of identities and backgrounds. With at least 30 female-led acts, 13 mixed-gender groups, and representation from non-binary artists, the festival continues to push for gender diversity. Furthermore, 44 artists identify as people of color, adding to the vibrant mosaic of voices on display. Whether you're drawn to the mainstage anthems or the underground DJ sets—of which there are 65 this year—this year’s edition offers a unique and inclusive celebration of music and artistry."
